<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-10-07T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-10-07T14:00:00-05:00" n="327" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d327">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Pacific War/551: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-10-07T14:00:00-05:00">October 7,
                                    1941—2 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>642. Reference Department’s 633, October 2, 9 p.m., also Saigon’s 102,
                            October 1, 8 a.m.,<note n="3" xml:id="d327fn1">Telegram No. 102 not
                                printed.</note> and Hanoi’s 149, October 3, 5 p.m., which have been
                            repeated to you, Japanese actions in Indochina.</p>
                        <p>If you have not already taken up this matter with the Foreign Minister
                            the Department suggests that you do so at the first opportunity.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>